elements.2211.03009_ee1d86667244b34af7a0e8cbb64a3: Mood inference with mobile sensing data has been studied in ubicomp literature over the last decade
elements.2211.03009_3146ef71b3e74a013dc23c2d3d8b7: This inference enables context-aware and personalized user experiences in general mobile apps and valuable feedback and interventions in mobile health apps
elements.2211.03009_a848d2bb2f4501e575ceba7c87243: However, even though model generalization issues have been highlighted in many studies, the focus has always been on improving the accuracies of models using different sensing modalities and machine learning techniques, with datasets collected in homogeneous populations
elements.2211.03009_335924debaba11f2b402fa101b1b4: In contrast, less attention has been given to studying the performance of mood inference models to assess whether models generalize to new countries
elements.2211.03009_0615ca0bcad2947f18d010dc3d967: In this study, we collected a mobile sensing dataset with 329K self-reports from 678 participants in eight countries (China, Denmark, India, Italy, Mexico, Mongolia, Paraguay, UK) to assess the effect of geographical diversity on mood inference models
elements.2211.03009_555c5f3013c94b56262877c925a12: We define and evaluate country-specific (trained and tested within a country), continent-specific (trained and tested within a continent), country-agnostic (tested on a country not seen on training data), and multi-country (trained and tested with multiple countries) approaches trained on sensor data for two mood inference tasks with population-level (non-personalized) and hybrid (partially personalized) models
elements.2211.03009_8d9510dbb95efda5fc5de9ccf5195: We show that partially personalized country-specific models perform the best yielding area under the receiver operating characteristic curve (AUROC) scores of the range 0.78-0.98 for two-class (negative vs. positive valence) and 0.76-0.94 for three-class (negative vs. neutral vs. positive valence) inference
elements.2211.03009_2077ffff24ce4a2040931deec7560: Further, with the country-agnostic approach, we show that models do not perform well compared to country-specific settings, even when models are partially personalized
elements.2211.03009_d19a0ac655b8cf28df1bcd50fb10a: We also show that continent-specific models outperform multi-country models in the case of Europe
elements.2211.03009_54a91c3b126ca2703f0754825f0fb: Overall, we uncover generalization issues of mood inference models to new countries and how the geographical similarity of countries might impact mood inference.

elements.2211.03009_8d08bd9135ec964d6936a97404f19: Mental well-being related issues are common among young adults due to a plethora of personal and societal reasons such as leaving home, study workload, poor financial stability, and complex social relationships
elements.2211.03009_b0ff07611537fc9620cccadfc3213: These issues are even more prominent in the post-pandemic world, where social relationships have taken a toll due to more emphasis on remote work/study settings
elements.2211.03009_15d6052f037e8aecd01b4734172a0: Some studies have shown that this emerging lifestyle has affected phone usage behavior as well
elements.2211.03009_ca75675abf3d8f20701493a9fc59c: Further, declining mental well-being conditions could lead to adverse outcomes such as substance abuse and suicidal thoughts
elements.2211.03009_e29ed7da72c887456c0a4041bc6b1: In this context, prior research has discussed the potential of timely and accurate mood tracking for both personal and clinical care
elements.2211.03009_163800ea8021b00c8a7c1f1877e0b: Ecological momentary assessments (EMAs) and survey questionnaires are commonly used for mood tracking
elements.2211.03009_41bc7de2b8959f1389bf85288f06e: However, such techniques are burdensome to users, and prior work has shown that it is difficult to sustain the practice of reporting for long periods unless there is a strong motivation
elements.2211.03009_1bc46f45bf06f14db6df996ec9c38: As a possible alternative, multi-modal sensors in smartphones could be used to infer mood unobtrusively with reasonable accuracies
elements.2211.03009_8feb318ae8043c5ec5ba50c8d7ecc: According to prior work in psychology and social sciences, physiological aspects, including mood, are perceived and expressed differently in different countries, cultures, and societies
elements.2211.03009_ebb674b8f10a47e869fb5841a76c0: According to a cross-country study by Becht et al.
elements.2211.03009_7548424e1b5cd4fe58871a2b9ad50: , mood and related behaviors could vary based on a person's culture, and perceptions and beliefs regarding different moods stemming from one's culture
elements.2211.03009_e48d1825cac370ea94b3994c15022: However, prior work in mobile sensing does not study the effect of the geographical diversity of users (e.g., country of residence) on smartphone sensing-based mood inference models
elements.2211.03009_3e55977a58dee6a7a92291da294ff: Issues of generalization and fairness with regard to the geographical diversity of data sources have been discussed extensively in domains such as computer vision, speech, and natural language processing
elements.2211.03009_6db92e91420f5da12c4a2ef50da9c: For example, gender classification models trained with data predominantly from the USA have performed poorly on people of African and Asian descent
elements.2211.03009_12b7785a9a692fe5f02945abc2798: Many geographical-related biases (e.g., Indian brides being recognized as dancers, etc.) have been shown in models trained with the imagenet dataset, in which a majority of data is from western countries
elements.2211.03009_2eb6eabbea0105e4724a1f243c651: Such findings have uncovered issues in data collection practices and helped shape research directions to address issues related to diversity and biases
elements.2211.03009_63368bf0d18509ac2c10f2115690f: In this context, many prior mobile sensing studies that attempt inferences regarding well-being related aspects highlighted that models are trained in specific countries, and the generalization of techniques for other countries or regions should be explored further
elements.2211.03009_c737b1e496f4e07c4e8cac597131b: However, mood inference studies have focused on only one or two countries for data collection
elements.2211.03009_85c34941264b454f68d9bdb45fb33: or have not considered the diversity of data sources in terms of the country, even when data were collected from multiple countries
elements.2211.03009_6d16a85b7ab7b23773b95641e67d0: emphasized the need for generalization and reproducibility of sensing-based models for mental well-being-related outcomes
elements.2211.03009_d5ccbe8facfaf9a8f2b4561749277: However, even though examining gender, age, and occupation-related diversity is feasible even within the same country, examining geographical diversity requires a considerable effort in conducting the same study, with the same protocol, in several geographic regions because studies are time-consuming and expensive; and logistical difficulties in conducting experiments such as language barriers, technology barriers, differences in motivating use cases and required incentives
elements.2211.03009_48ba5122d7f8b7301d13da658dace: Hence, studies that examine the geographical diversity of mobile sensing-based inferences are rare
elements.2211.03009_b73dda40a34c3537059bc58b694b4: In this paper, we study and compare the performance of country-specific, country-agnostic, and multi-country approaches for mood inference
elements.2211.03009_bd857965dd0782b59f0e6d98b4e09: In addition, we also examine the effects of model personalization and generalization to new geographically diverse countries
elements.2211.03009_8ebc0e5aedc2f2cff31741ee95e5b: To our knowledge, this is one of the first studies to examine the effect of geographical diversity of users on smartphone sensing-based mood inference models, hence shedding light on distributional shift related issues
elements.2211.03009_b31e0147e174ca0e303f867f7e21a: Considering these aspects, we ask three research questions.
elements.2211.03009_3f9b507228bc1dee77d85f5745ddc: What behavioral and contextual characteristics around mood reports of college students (from eight countries spanning Europe, Asia, and Latin America) can be extracted from the analysis of smartphone sensing and self-report data?
elements.2211.03009_b87f6b7a145f75db316b865210144: How do smartphone sensing-based mood inference models perform in different countries (country-specific)? Can a model trained in one/more countries be deployed in another country not seen on training data to achieve reasonable accuracies, hence generalizing well (country-agnostic)?
elements.2211.03009_2615d058650d223901ac6b676fde1: How do country-specific or continent-specific models perform as compared to a multi-country model?
elements.2211.03009_3a47f6fbcc8a227453f3f55ed513a: By addressing the above research questions, this paper provides the following contributions:
elements.2211.03009_87fbec7de0ed7d814e9b0f18f27ac: We conducted a new smartphone-based data collection campaign among 678 participants in eight countries (China, Denmark, India, Italy, Mexico, Mongolia, Paraguay, UK) representing Europe, Asia, and Latin America to study their everyday mood and behavior
elements.2211.03009_a348d6047f5b10e397f8b77ee2380: During the study, we collected 329,974 fully complete self-reports
elements.2211.03009_68902bd1ced7390ffd2357d439901: In addition, we also collected rich passive sensing data with continuous sensing (activity type, step count, location, cellular, wifi, bluetooth, proximity, etc.) and interaction sensing (app usage, touch events, user presence, screen-on/off episodes, notifications, etc.) throughout the deployment
elements.2211.03009_4d88e0e607efdd656d1e270fec64b: First, we found that negative mood reports in all countries would increase from morning to night
elements.2211.03009_5896db290370e547bd2211cc02dfd: Moreover, with statistical analysis, we found that the features that help infer mood are different across countries
elements.2211.03009_006992a4de9c78925209cb82cb5cf: However, the best features included both continuous and interaction sensing modalities in all countries.
elements.2211.03009_a634d76842e31f9efcaba35dcf675: We found that the country-specific approach performs reasonably for both two-class and three-class mood inferences with AUROC scores in the range of 0.76-0.98 with hybrid (i.e., partially personalized) models
elements.2211.03009_d92cb204aafe9d08b59dfe21b4f19: However, we noticed that across both two-class and three-class inferences, models do not generalize well to other countries, where AUROC scores drop to the range of 0.46-0.55 on average in the population-level (i.e., non-personalized) setting and 0.66-0.73 in the hybrid setting
elements.2211.03009_0c89c32b52d2135b86b96556b378a: These findings raise the significance of discussing issues of generalization of mobile sensing-based models to different world regions.
elements.2211.03009_8f478b2636c989e945e160cd9a2fa: In the hybrid setting, we found that multi-country models do not perform as well as country-specific models even though they achieved an AUROC of 0.81
elements.2211.03009_8a6ffa39ffee132f61627067b81dc: However, they performed better than continent-specific models built for Asia and worse than the one built for Europe
elements.2211.03009_279e513272e417d3799bc25b04f38: Even though the performance differences were not high, this again highlights that building a model within European countries leads to higher performance and better generalization for those countries than using multi-country or even some country-specific models
elements.2211.03009_008c18e423608254a3b5e7fb2b27b: A possible explanation is that the European countries under study (Italy, Denmark, UK) might share some daily behavioral patterns
elements.2211.03009_4352e33d2992f99a7a28f5a2c7432: In contrast, the three countries in Asia under study (China, India, Mongolia) have less similarity regarding daily patterns
elements.2211.03009_d8a96369d6f749fd678fb94eb29eb: Hence, these findings point toward the benefit of considering the geographical/cultural diversity of data collection on smartphone sensing-based mood inference models.

elements.2211.03009_70f40d568404952ec3236f2274cfd: Considerations for Research in Mobile Sensing Involving Geographic Diversity
elements.2211.03009_53fcaa4aad7016752b098e50f55d7: Across different geographical regions and cultures, behavior is mediated by inherent beliefs, presses, and affordances of physical and/or socio-cultural environments
elements.2211.03009_07afaaf8045b049e2742ee9306446: Even for behaviors that are similar across cultures, the psychological meaning of those behaviors might not be the same due to
elements.2211.03009_332fd5c869aced0286e84b107b71c: : (a) Certain behaviors that are acceptable in certain countries/cultures are not perceived as normative or appropriate in other countries
elements.2211.03009_a3eca3239d7640e66baeb88e98ca3: ; (b) The same behavior might be indicative of different outcomes/functions
elements.2211.03009_86564e7450bac027071fc7ef32929: For example, while cycling is everyday behavior in certain regions (e.g., Aalborg, Denmark), it might only be used for exercise in other areas (e.g., Ulanbatoor, Mongolia); and (c) Different behaviors might be indicative of a similar outcome/function
elements.2211.03009_3c1ac42abf451d60064a6352f8ddf: For example, while people in some countries might perform cycling for exercise, people in other countries might prefer going to the gym for exercise
elements.2211.03009_f5cb7bd57f559a5fcb260ce14c23f: Why people cycle will depend on many contextual and cultural factors such as road safety, availability of public transport, alternative exercise options, weather conditions, and perceptions about cycling in a specific geographical region
elements.2211.03009_7d83d8b7f71416ed0ad4b3bed3ddf: Given that smartphone sensors can capture such physical activities (e.g., Google Activity Recognition API
elements.2211.03009_392b0329815af4a8fde385f36e9c0: and other activity engines built by researchers
elements.2211.03009_a8a28b51f098d09edfe753e506088: ) and are used to infer more complex variables
elements.2211.03009_314c28b6f1fd26b0fd63a6046a353: , invariably, such behavioral differences across geographical areas could affect mood inference models that leverage activity data from accelerometers and location
elements.2211.03009_eba86585ce89def97bede72cba64c: In addition, device-mediated behavior or phone usage behavior could also vary between geographical areas depending on cultural norms, weather conditions (e.g., the phone usage behavior while walking outside in a cold vs. a hot country), network coverage, and subscription plans (e.g., people in countries where internet plans are expensive might turn off internet frequently, people in countries where the used phones are old might turn off Wifi and location sensors often to save battery of the phone, etc.), and availability of alternative equipment that could serve similar functionality (e.g., using a laptop for zoom calls instead of the phone, hence showing differences in the sensed app usage behavior)
elements.2211.03009_652b6c7c9525caf180bcb6d05d43e: Given that mood inference models in prior work have used both continuous (activity types, step counts, location, proximity, wifi, etc.) and interaction (typing and touch events, user presence, application usage, screen on and off events, etc.) sensing modalities to examine/infer mood and related psychological constructs, how behaviors and contexts captured with smartphones affect mood inference in different countries is worth investigating.

elements.2211.03009_0e221333926c3fd029b513d937af0: Hence, there are studies that infer aspects like mood

elements.2211.03009_e336f016924c2c8890cf5b17c1faf: using personalization (user-level) with a dataset collected from 32 individuals

elements.2211.03009_cb050d4a26dac7b01295193570aad: They also showed that binary mood captured with the circumplex mood model could be inferred with an accuracy of 70
elements.2211.03009_b65f937e6dfca43f1365a0ef03a4b: Some studies examined mood instability derived using mood reports, with phone sensor data
elements.2211.03009_7bf8911650c0293f1228bcf0c2930: In our work, we look into inferring mood valence with population-level and hybrid models
elements.2211.03009_e47e9685fe0063a191ff29c4305ba: However, we are more interested in examining (a) the similarities and differences in mood models for different countries; and (b) the generalization of models to unseen countries, both of which have not been examined in prior work
elements.2211.03009_57c3a1ee55a84f57262764c6033dc: highlighted, there is a lack of reproducibility and generalization of machine learning models across studies in this domain
elements.2211.03009_f6405e3fc509ee0dd052f5313ae64: We believe the results presented in this study would be a step in the right direction for better awareness of these issues in examining the characteristics and generalization of smartphone sensing-based mood inference models across different geographical regions.
elements.2211.03009_45ff46d868bdb38d75fa89a38562a: Study Design, Data Collection, and Feature Extraction
elements.2211.03009_2f67357b4bf46f6867b841f6b2d2a: With a team representing computer science, social sciences, user experience design, and ethics from institutions in over ten countries, we designed an exploratory study and developed a mobile sensing application to collect passive smartphone sensing and self-report data from participants about their everyday life behavior and well-being
elements.2211.03009_3f8d7be6c886259a0eec234b6ff30: The ultimate goal of this deployment was to study their behavior, including aspects such as activity, social context, location, mood, and sleep quality from a mobile sensing standpoint and also to consider various diversity aspects that could potentially affect sensing-based inferences (ranging from geographical region and gender to personality and values)
elements.2211.03009_d0be9a5fd874bc76fd0aaab1949c1: The study is summarized in Figure
elements.2211.03009_67cae1cfc38e0a310127696fc7c3a: The study design consisted of two main components: (a) LimeSurvey component to collect survey responses during pre and mid-study phases; and (b) Mobile sensing app to collect sensor data and self-reports
elements.2211.03009_99ef51cf4db76e509c49d6503d8cc: A technical report regarding the study procedure and future plans for dataset access is available in
elements.2211.03009_ca0e721d45d878e1a3c1b36097e94: Survey responses were captured from participants with three questionnaires sent to them before and during the pilot at three different times
elements.2211.03009_40314e505c2edd2c21043ebaffcb4: This was done to ensure that the burden on participants was reasonable
elements.2211.03009_9d285ed93fc43dc534ae0cf1d37c1: These questionnaires were administered through the LimeSurvey platform
elements.2211.03009_fef9cda501692aeb26b0ee272ec90: The primary objective of this questionnaire was to capture diversity attributes of participants from different perspectives
elements.2211.03009_d71c7020ce0c03357a9cac3fbb759: As the first step, basic demographic information was captured, including gender, age, sex, degree program, and socioeconomic status
elements.2211.03009_5fddf88c58c98df72ea22498a80f0: Then, in an attempt to capture the psychosocial profile, the 20-item Big Five Inventory (BFI)
elements.2211.03009_5e655b135614f9720d31a14baaaec: Finally, there were several questions regarding social relationships (virtual and real) and cultural consumption that they were interested in.
elements.2211.03009_cd952ecc2d9c081d11651d3012e98: The objective of the first questionnaire was to gather more detailed information about personality using the Jungian Scale on Personality Types
elements.2211.03009_9d0de2aaafbccccd118a5a6ff54e6: In addition, questions regarding physical activity and sports, cooking and shopping habits, transport methodologies, and cultural activities were captured
elements.2211.03009_301310a388a8a0f905a3487b1a0ec: The second questionnaire consisted of the Multiple Intelligences Profiling Questionnaire
elements.2211.03009_a186ce8e0bdca05a330622596241b: This also contained several open-ended questionnaires about the mobile app user experience.
elements.2211.03009_495069d6f22648bf1bcb7f4a56e2d: An Android mobile application was used to capture the everyday behavior of participants using short in-situ self-report questions
elements.2211.03009_89a17c99597560dba1239339d05f6: The app was developed such that data would be stored in an SQLite database on the phone, and later when the phone is connected to a Wifi network, data would be uploaded to the main server and free up the local phone storage
elements.2211.03009_84b56574633f9882d8764bd16647c: In addition, the app could send push notifications by using Google Firebase as a notification broker
elements.2211.03009_24241f44ac26edef0778ded2f462f: Hence, the three main components of the application are: (1) a push notification system that would send periodical reminders to participants to fill in self-reports; (2) mobile time diaries to capture self-reports; and (3) a smartphone sensing component to collect passive sensing data from multiple modalities.
elements.2211.03009_03e9a41892a5f6a569102ab4ad309: Given the nature of the study and the requirement to capture behavioral and situational data in a particular moment, the app sent reminders for participants to fill in in-situ self-reports regarding their everyday life behavior around 20 times throughout the day
elements.2211.03009_a63d4382fff675349461697f32dc2: In addition, start-of-the-day and end-of-the-day questionnaires were administered at the beginning and end of the day
elements.2211.03009_f7564127ef84f83fb8eaf5563bd3f: When a notification was not clicked and a participant did not complete the self-report within two hours, the notification expired, and a new notification would be sent later
elements.2211.03009_8490f305594660b5255f5f4bb5d52: This allowed to keep track of participant compliance (e.g., how many self-reports were answered from the total number of notifications sent).
elements.2211.03009_c0efc6b32659b441f847377e646c9: The start-of-the-day questionnaire was sent to participants at 8 am each day
elements.2211.03009_cee11e2b813dcbc50dbddde030530: It only had two questions with five-point likert scales (very good to very bad): (i) sleep quality; and (ii) expectations about the day
elements.2211.03009_0689ec10825b4eccfab66dea69879: The end-of-the-day questionnaire was sent to participants at 10 pm and asked them (a) to rate their day (five-point likert scale; very good to very bad); (b) if they had any problems during the day (open response), and (c) how did they solve them (open response)
elements.2211.03009_74363a68d510937d65d84a496e579: The time diary was sent to users once every 30-60 minutes
elements.2211.03009_d568332a5dd7235411903da2ecb2e: While this allowed capturing longitudinal behavior granularly, it also introduced user burden
elements.2211.03009_b280c82ea4692eaf19a5f7ade1d87: Therefore, the time diary was designed to minimize user burden and reduce completion time
elements.2211.03009_6a9a4c49c1b6742a904c04fcfa4d2: Hence, after several iterations of discussions, only four questions were included in this component: (i) current activity: 34 activities including eating, working, attending a lecture, etc.; (ii) semantic location: 26 categories including home, workplace, university, restaurant, etc.; (iii) social context: 8 categories including alone, with the partner, family member/s, friends, etc.; and (iv) current mood: five-point likert scale to capture the valence of the circumplex mood model
elements.2211.03009_0273a1d53731c8408a2bb07ffe044: , this is the variable we chose as this paper's primary focus.

elements.2211.03009_a0454ca3429f151e82e372de7a697: Invitations, Pre-Study Diversity Questionnaire, and Participants
elements.2211.03009_f2c4d7cf068b5d04fbdefee931d04: This was the first of the three phases of the data collection
elements.2211.03009_eb308966b92ec2d5a2be2c50c4892: This phase started by sending an email containing the survey description, the invitation to the first questionnaire, and information on the second part of the data collection (sensing component) via university mailing lists

elements.2211.03009_69d9d23b654d11b243ff1c94839cd: Out of the set of people who were contacted, 13398 participants filled in the pre-study diversity questionnaire
elements.2211.03009_11685338ab7cadd6973f9255b35b8: Then, a subset of the eligible participants was selected to participate in the second part of the study, which was done with the mobile app

elements.2211.03009_1049e007fa59df903167e9cfbc470: Behavioral and Contextual Characteristics Around Mood Reports Extracted from Sensor Data and Self-Reports (RQ1)
elements.2211.03009_c7f5173eb49ead5a7869ba0d161fc: shows the distribution of mood labels for the eight countries
elements.2211.03009_175a86e3ace994ad93a601c954732: We observed fewer labels for the ânegativeâ and âvery negativeâ classes compared to the âneutralâ, âpositiveâ, and âvery positiveâ classes
elements.2211.03009_1d28ba8c4fdb4a056e93ba80a70b3: , except for China, where there were more âvery positiveâ reports than âpositiveâ or âneutralâ reports, all other countries had âpositiveâ as the majority label
elements.2211.03009_cb19dbc32b1649e84133212409b52: This behavior of skewed reporting is common in studies about valence
elements.2211.03009_b2c925867dbc485068a4ea91c396c: Furthermore, we plot the hourly distribution of mood reports in Figure
elements.2211.03009_b47d06934be25d35b94b8e89bf7b5: , across all countries, we could see more self-reports in the morning compared to the afternoon or evening

elements.2211.03009_b2cc3cc2a21983c75825c388b92ac: This means that users had a more positive mood after waking up and around the morning
elements.2211.03009_5f7a86f3c315a9f68ce88aa64e925: Interestingly, we also observed that the curve for Mongolia indicates late sleep and late wake-up, according to reports, which the partner institution later confirmed to be consistent with the routines of students in the country
elements.2211.03009_b474aedeeace1da25bacf91be42f7: , we also noticed that negative valence reports increase with time in most countries
elements.2211.03009_bc67ae4fa4cfb7cc26a67bc21b6f0: This is in line with prior studies about mood and stress levels increasing with the time of the day
elements.2211.03009_b92e86dd0caaea36a95ad072acf09: , participants' social context and semantic location labels were captured with time diaries, in addition to mood

elements.2211.03009_193bd11cc5c1a38ab7345fab5e4d1: These two aspects were chosen because prior work has shown that being alone and being away from home could affect mental well-being and behavior
elements.2211.03009_66fa4944d6f4f7c9e3c7a7818a2a2: In the figure, on the X-axis, the eight countries are shown
elements.2211.03009_305a1bc92db8a0bfea479b1bb1186: On the Y-axis, the percentage of self-reports is shown

elements.2211.03009_2ccadd8689f3881e4d0ab72c57df2: The primary goal of this paper is to investigate aspects related to mood inference, personalization, and generalization to different countries using smartphone sensing data
elements.2211.03009_fe7e5e6fedb779385d9743259e76b: As described and defined in Figure
elements.2211.03009_af8adb91dbe1d2ada70995078bd27: , we use two model types: population-level and hybrid, to examine personalization to individuals, and four modeling approaches: country-specific, continent-specific, country-agnostic, and multi-country, to examine generalization and country-wise performance
elements.2211.03009_ff3ce76350d671de2455bcda16e19: Hence, this section will describe the operationalization of the experimental protocol
elements.2211.03009_b783a9f41de0139201477f4f157c6: Initially, we conducted country-specific experiments with different model types such as random forest (RF), gradient boosting, support vector classification, XGBoost, AdaBoost, and multi-layer perceptron neural networks
elements.2211.03009_aa67b0f7422920317be0d5c63f924: We obtained the best results for a larger majority of inferences with RFs
elements.2211.03009_d11f6c6abd38b49c6ea597a74a90e: In addition, these models allow interpreting results better because they provide Gini feature importance values for trained models
elements.2211.03009_cb39903dca7791bdd79bb21323825: Because of these reasons and space limitations, we will only report results for RF models with default parameters in this paper
elements.2211.03009_d2a5ea4f99967a09ee1f224a3c875: Further, to fill in missing values of the dataset, we used k-nearest-neighbor (kNN) imputation
elements.2211.03009_d9735aca47bf4a74888ce9cea922f: In addition, we report all the results with the area under the receiver operating characteristic curve (AUROC)
elements.2211.03009_af34062e3180bf170583aa02e546d: because they provide a better assessment of performance when dealing with imbalanced data (when used with macro averaging which gives equal emphasis to all classes in an inference)
elements.2211.03009_75df74ffb56c419961af888621baa: While we provided a basic description of model types in Table
elements.2211.03009_ad083528f39c21c7cff4fa35fed41: , the operationalization of models is given below.
elements.2211.03009_e05b0bc885cf71d13ff0d22579632: : Since this represents a scenario where models are deployed to a set of users unseen in model training, we use the leave-n-participants-out strategy when testing models
elements.2211.03009_6c7b3da92dc7696fd2c5a260fb78c: This is an extension of leave-one-out cross-validation, where we consider
elements.2211.03009_56e06de359ecb9c9ee3f4bdd82535: users in testing instead of one
elements.2211.03009_875dfc39706fc3eb0b3bc313417d8: Hence, if the number of users in the considered population is

elements.2211.03009_9c05b44ebfa5f3e3d8bb9afccd332: of their data would be used for testing to be coherent with hybrid models (stratified based on users and mood labels), and data from the rest of the
elements.2211.03009_0ff597398171a35b7903832640458: users would be used for the training split
elements.2211.03009_98c36084e2f923df581b9617afea1: Then, experiments were repeated ten times by randomly sampling
elements.2211.03009_f9d11348d33d2c7260a2780d63b94: users, and the results were averaged.
elements.2211.03009_e299ee374db21397f413b712d05d7: : Since this represents a scenario where models are deployed to a set of users already seen in model training (hence partially personalized models), we first use the leave-n-participants-out strategy similar to PLM

elements.2211.03009_31ec8cc35ad40c81d10bb4310abaa: In addition, an equal number of data points to the number of data points added to the training set from the testing set would be removed randomly to make the number of data points in the training and testing sets for HM and PLM equal making them more comparable
elements.2211.03009_603ff91ae45330dd1f4311693e6b1: Finally, experiments were repeated ten times by randomly sampling
elements.2211.03009_b6b8776f0e64728425ca9cd8fdda1: Using the above two model types, we conducted the experiments using four approaches

elements.2211.03009_a85b6730ee75cf88844996259a079: The country-agnostic approach examines how models trained in one or a few countries generalize to a new country
elements.2211.03009_bf0207bd4688c798b3137d0e36c6f: With PLM and HM model types, we examine how personalization affects model performance when models are deployed to countries unseen on training data

elements.2211.03009_5ffc36c314ff8f5801a02403e71b4: In this section, we discuss the main findings of the paper, and highlight limitations and future work.
elements.2211.03009_0eebd4450e095d5d73493693b025c: In the country-specific setting, PLMs did not perform well across countries, with the highest performance for both two-class and three-class inferences coming from Mexico, with an AUROC of 0.62
elements.2211.03009_1fb87a687ef6c8300a4f570b07fd3: However, performance increased significantly, with HMs showing the effect of personalization within countries
elements.2211.03009_cdd9989edfc483840728b675661f2: Comparable performance gains were observed for the multi-country setting as well
elements.2211.03009_5f3be63f738da712f05c62397c058: However, country-specific models (AUROC scores of 0.78-0.98 for two-class and 0.76-0.94 for three-class) would be preferred over multi-country models (0.83 and 0.79 for two and three classes, respectively)
elements.2211.03009_5ca896561a504a583cbc69ede94ea: Then, in the country-agnostic setting, we observed that even HMs performed poorly compared to the country-specific setting
elements.2211.03009_b3b25b2b4afbdf55d49dc4a20936d: This means that if a model is trained in a different country, even if it is personalized to a person in another country, the model might not perform as well as a country-specific model that is personalized to a person in the same country
elements.2211.03009_25eb591aeb134407f71df8370f7d1: However, we also observed that models perform relatively better in culturally similar countries (i.e., within Europe)
elements.2211.03009_64e12314811fe2c74489d1085102a: Within Asia, even though countries are in the same geographic region, cultural differences (i.e., India and China have different cultures and behaviors) could be one reason that did not allow models to perform better
elements.2211.03009_a04df115f0dd3d2f8ad2ef7f6a156: Finally, building continent-specific models for Europe worked reasonably better than for Asia or a multi-country setting
elements.2211.03009_0a35831545efe9941535a99bc3aa3: Please note that the number of participants in several of these countries remained small, and so we cannot make any strong assertions.

elements.2211.03009_27825bbb006f98572e7ced1486c86: , diversity and diversity awareness are topics in machine learning that have gained importance in the recent past, and increasing generalization and decreasing biases in models for different populations are two fundamental goals discussed in this domain
elements.2211.03009_77d6031d99c7826e09cf18806b07c: According to them, diversity is achieved in machine learning with data diversification (maximizing the informativeness in training data such that the model fits data better), model diversification (increased diversity in model parameters leading to better learning), and inference diversification (model provides choices/information with more complementary information)
elements.2211.03009_c0fc963b3832ed63af3709a8a32e1: Our study examined diversity awareness, primarily with data diversification
elements.2211.03009_4c045f73f1c5c439f13995b957507: Since the whole data collection was done to emphasize the need for diversity awareness in machine learning-based mobile sensing systems, we defined diversity based on social practice theory
elements.2211.03009_b0b15ecd35a0913761ee1c913939d: Accordingly, diversity is a complex and multi-layered construct that does not exist within individuals but surfaces when two or more individuals interact
elements.2211.03009_c1c3ec1e541b209cd87c987883b3d: Considering these conceptions, data and model diversity can be achieved by considering various types of diversity attributes ranging from country of residence, gender, and age, to personality, values, etc.
elements.2211.03009_4fcbebe0045e6a19bcaf545df149d: In this paper, we focused on âcountry of residenceâ as an attribute for analysis because of the way mood is perceived and expressed, as well as phone usage and everyday behavior are different in countries around the world

elements.2211.03009_065193050ea94ec61e8250365360f: In this study, we considered the geographical diversity of users when building smartphone sensing-based mood inference models
elements.2211.03009_0a9b9790435bfd5e73f05d827eea2: Hence, our primary construct of diversity is the `country of residence'
elements.2211.03009_1e05284606b985ddeb8b2b00e5d48: However, depending on the city, even though it is within the same country, the cultural composition of students could vary significantly
elements.2211.03009_33300fe1dd0fb72766996180c6100: For example, our specific university in London, UK, is considered more diverse and has a high international student population compared to our specific university in India

elements.2211.03009_b26ed9545874636ffb7c6071e263a: Mood is a self-reported internal state and thus constitutes sensitive information
elements.2211.03009_5073aedac4c00ade3e5e3d94814ae: Ethical implications related to inference of affective states have been discussed in previous literature in affective computing
elements.2211.03009_833b320698b0c5a7ffa8d934f2e4f: From the perspective of possible applications beyond supporting research on youth well-being, as we do here, it is fundamental that human-centered principles are followed and limit their use to cases that benefit individuals and avoid potential harm.
elements.2211.03009_8a61bf26553ac09e81fc071b4948c: In this paper, we showed how mood inferences could be done in the context of a mobile sensing application
elements.2211.03009_debee0667e980b557e1ae7be8ad72: In addition, we also showed how models lack generalization to unseen countries and the need for personalization
elements.2211.03009_584fecc8e33c41777c4fb3c5329b9: However, a limitation of this study is that the study was conducted during the pandemic
elements.2211.03009_387e46c5c961e23f8377e44750ac9: During the data collection time period in 2020, many countries have imposed different measures to curb the coronavirus
elements.2211.03009_13f603a97dd5608491418792930bc: However, it is worth noting that, except for China, where strict lockdown measures were not present, universities have been in remote work/study mode in all the other countries
elements.2211.03009_c0801b22ab34e013d45e1b934bf34: Hence, most students engaged in their studies from home
elements.2211.03009_c27ff1013683ba984df4b8cae1eef: This could be the reason why there are many app usage, touch event, proximity, and wifi related features informative about mood according to Figure
elements.2211.03009_83f2efb3efa1bd5e9925763c7beca: It is also worth noting that the seasons in each country during the data collection period were different
elements.2211.03009_d094f68218ea1f864333e368bcdee: On the positive side, none of the countries were in extreme winter or summer seasons
elements.2211.03009_5b0d7c2fd988c262d93d539ed8d1a: The September-November time period in European countries is the fall season, and none of those countries faced extreme cold weather conditions during that period
elements.2211.03009_bf04f3b549240e4a5715392f3defb: At this time, the season in Mongolia was comparable to European countries like Denmark or UK
elements.2211.03009_c7b0b3bf2fb7cc79b7d58146b00ff: All the other countries had comparatively higher temperatures
elements.2211.03009_78382217ca74efafb195bc5cfac60: However, given that students in all the sites were affected by movement restriction measures and were stuck at home, we believe that weather conditions might not have affected the study as much compared to a time period when student behavior in outdoor environments would significantly change based on weather conditions
elements.2211.03009_907d5ab6b4c2a3cc750ae1788a436: However, the results should be understood and interpreted with this limitation in mind
elements.2211.03009_00113954fe74d063f746f4cbea4fd: Future work could explore the effects of seasons and weather conditions on mobile sensing-based inferences.
elements.2211.03009_ed50f3d94829b059a319d0ca75972: Domain Adaptation for Multi-Modal Mobile Sensing
elements.2211.03009_ea53ab750ec93bc288e0e4b5979e9: In this paper, we highlighted the issue of generalization and the possible distributional shifts in a mobile sensing dataset collected with the same protocol in different countries
elements.2211.03009_bad3d6fd82074f0054769f173f947: Even though issues of generalization, biases, and domain shifts have been discussed extensively in other domains such as computer vision
elements.2211.03009_ed3a3d1cbd2f437c6c47bdbc45bc7: , smartphone/mobile sensing studies have not focused on those aspects extensively thus far
elements.2211.03009_e6474775a94230a02e71a7168aa3a: Even though we provide evidence of the fundamental issue, we did not go into depth about finding a potential solution for that issue, as it is not within the scope of this paper (especially given page limits and extensive work that would be needed)
elements.2211.03009_f4b22f2884dbede946d7be5e08dde: Further, even though we showed that model personalization (hybrid setting) could minimize domain shift to an extent, other advanced techniques inspired by the work related to domain shift/adaptation in other domains could provide cues for solving such problems in mobile sensing
elements.2211.03009_a76da96190a685084ed6141de6faa: Recent studies also suggest that domain adaptation techniques for time series data are limited
elements.2211.03009_97878b8165f5d21ed4752699abbb1: For example, a longstanding problem in the human activity recognition (HAR) domain is the wearing diversity of wearables in different body positions
elements.2211.03009_80b67eb13f66041371b227f29a1fd: The wearing diversity hinders the performance of HAR models
elements.2211.03009_2f95a17defb039c8fb63f01e3298e: A few recent studies suggested that unsupervised domain adaptation could be a solution for wearing diversity issues
elements.2211.03009_86a708d1ddc713857b06a1fd05108: explored domain adaptation for similar datasets captured from people from two age groups
elements.2211.03009_f2185e2a9bb0e079cd01394c8cd5b: However, the above studies focused on time series accelerometer data, which are more straightforward than the multi-modal datasets we are working with within this study
elements.2211.03009_1d6f7254ca5f056a682d68df141df: Hence, to the best of our knowledge, a research gap lies in solving domain adaptation for multi-modal sensing data coming from smartphones and wearables
elements.2211.03009_7e64e62da0b5e01c424c11b05c0d8: In fact, in a recent study, Adler et al.
elements.2211.03009_5ca7967ff8170f956864cfdb52948: discussed the issue of generalization in multi-modal mobile sensing data and showed that lack of similarity across datasets collected in different time periods does not allow studying generalization of techniques to a greater depth
elements.2211.03009_ccd7de545a67f3fb82c824d09e46d: Therefore, with the dataset discussed in this paper, we believe solutions to domain adaptation and generalization could be explored further (not regarding generalization across time, but across geographically/culturally distinct areas), hence pushing the boundaries of multi-modal mobile sensing systems towards more real-world utility.
elements.2211.03009_5f615d8f5507b05c6e76685181cbd: This work has several limitations and areas that could be improved in future work
elements.2211.03009_6d46f81c74055579c3bb7ee7e98a3: First, the dataset used in this study is highly imbalanced, where there are fewer negative and very negative mood labels than neutral, positive, and very positive mood labels
elements.2211.03009_fce51b58fbda7b7cbf53378d9b627: However, this distribution is in a way similar to previous studies about valence
elements.2211.03009_6f8cd716b42da228d9171c2cfa0e0: Inherently, this also makes both inference tasks much harder
elements.2211.03009_8c589c7bd2fd97f27e6988712a7e1: On the other hand, there is an imbalance in the dataset regarding data per country, where Italy and Mongolia had a significantly higher number of self-reports
elements.2211.03009_1f358774618b7b5366f5b9fc71ac5: In addition to the experimental results that we reported with imbalanced datasets, we conducted experiments with stratified down-sampled datasets for each country (each country having samples equal to the number of India, which had the lowest number of self-reports)
elements.2211.03009_d69a26a6c187179b9feeb4c6bb2cf: While we reported some results for balanced cases in multi-country and continent-specific cases, more extensive analysis could be done to explore that aspect further
elements.2211.03009_689ad642d6447f642ea3f04c49f3f: Hence, diversity-aware sampling strategies could be explored in future work to mitigate biases in mobile sensing-based inference models
elements.2211.03009_1a19050edad35084c3963b4f6898a: Further, we only considered valence in the circumplex mood model in this study
elements.2211.03009_fc6e0d2495f20a789bb8183f66205: Other time diary questions were used to capture other behaviors and contexts, and we did not want to overburden users with multiple questions or lengthy questionnaires
elements.2211.03009_f3878df87fcb9622ea287cf8aefed: However, we agree that collecting the arousal and understanding the geographical diversity of arousal inference could be studied in future work
elements.2211.03009_a9c99623fd25c17fae759c7bf2ba1: In addition, the clinical validity of the valence in the circumplex mood models might be questionable
elements.2211.03009_7aaf617c1728a063e51203e80be3d: Future work could look into conducting studies with more clinically valid instruments for mood inference
elements.2211.03009_00e23a0bb5d236816c8080e2e541b: In addition, in this paper, we did not use a 'wrapper' feature selection technique before training models because tree-based models, such as random forest, inherently use 'embedded' feature selection with Gini impurity to find a set of good features to build the trees with
elements.2211.03009_3e0cec159ba91942286fd5fa7fdd1: , especially when the feature space is small (i.e., around 100 in this dataset)
elements.2211.03009_bffa390fe38ffa6bf7bb33f864a5d: However, if the feature space was larger, the dataset size was smaller, or if another non-tree-based model was used, using feature selection is highly preferred
elements.2211.03009_27a2c07e4548bd9bb1956a1d62c57: Therefore, future work could also look into improving models based on feature selection and finding solutions to the issue of generalization using careful feature selection.
elements.2211.03009_5a5f403698717160c50de04ff48fd: In this exploratory study, we collected a mobile sensing dataset and around 329K self-reports from 678 participants in eight countries (China, Denmark, India, Italy, Mexico, Mongolia, Paraguay, UK) for over three weeks to assess the effect of geographical diversity on mood inference models
elements.2211.03009_4cbad527a75b3b5e6ac355da63178: We evaluated country-specific, continent-specific, country-agnostic, and multi-country approaches trained on sensor data for two mood inference tasks with population-level (non-personalized) and hybrid (partially personalized) models
elements.2211.03009_b2561936a37fbca05bd7d87a5241f: We showed that partially personalized country-specific models perform the best yielding AUROC scores in the range of 0.78-0.98 for two-class (negative vs. positive) and 0.76-0.94 for three-class (negative vs. neutral vs. positive) inference
elements.2211.03009_5f8e850fb385d59444145a91f5d61: Further, with the country-agnostic approach, we showed that models do not perform well compared to country-specific settings, even when models are partially personalized
elements.2211.03009_847fb7836a4d0c493ecf004b391d6: We also uncovered generalization issues of sensing-based mood inference models to new countries
elements.2211.03009_e995ac428ebbc9bf2b3b0551bff64: We hope that these findings will be of benefit to ubicomp researchers towards building future mobile sensing applications with an awareness of geographical diversity.
